			<item>
				<title>Version 2.3.0</title>
				<description><![CDATA[
					<h2>Major update</h2>
					<p>
						This is a major update of QuoteFix. In short, it adds a proper
						preference pane, advanced templating for attributions, and
						customized signature matching.
					</p>
					<h3>Changes</h3>
					<h4>General</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>the preferences for QuoteFix have been moved from the <i>Mail</i> menu to the Mail.app preferences window</li>
					</ul>
					<h4>Quotefixing</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>customized signature matching: you can now define a regular expression which is used to match signature separators</li>
						<li><b>new option:</b> increase quote level of attribution lines</li>
						<li><b>new option:</b> don't include a line of whitespace below the first-level quote</li>
						<li><b>new option:</b> "keep senders signature"</li>
						<li><b>new option:</b> "keep leading whitespace"</li>
						<li>better compatibility with Attachment Tamer</li>
					</ul>
					<h4>Customized attributions</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>previewing your customized attributions</li>
						<li>advanced templating (should be explicitely enabled in the <i>Advanced</i> preferences)</li>
						<li>use HTML to style your attributions</li>
					</ul>
				]]></description>
